        "subject": "LU-18135 scripts: bad iproute rt_tables path",
        "message": "LU-18135 scripts: bad iproute rt_tables path\n\nksocklnd-config fails in some distros where there is no config in\n/etc/iproute2, but in /usr/share/iproute2.\nTo fix that and keep the distro files untouched, we copy rt_tables\ninto /etc/iproute2 and modify it.\n\nFixes: 7f60b2b55 (\"LU-17006 lnet: set up routes for going across subnets\")\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-lnet\nSigned-off-by: Cyril Bordage <cbordage@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I0d633241d5dc2a22715e6959c6628476874059a8\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60250\nReviewed-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
